{
  "texts": [
    "However, just like with MBDTA, skilled users are necessary to understand how the program interacts with hardware features to ensure confidence in the estimates [38].The main drawback of MBPTA is its reliance on representative measurements and statistical methods to estimate the WCET, which introduces significant challenges.",
    "The presence of hardware acceleration elements such as cache memories and superscalar pipelines increases temporal variability and uncertainty, complicating the acquisition of reliable measurements.",
    "Additionally, MBPTA's accuracy heavily depends on the quality and representativeness of the collected data.",
    "If the data does not accurately capture the worst-case scenarios, the resulting WCET estimates may be unreliable, making it difficult to ensure the safety and predictability required for real-time systems [85].The main disadvantages of HYPTA are its early stage of development and lack of industrial deployment.",
    "The primary HYPTA technique is PUB."
  ]
}